OL,7,FOfficers discovered that McEnroe, of
OL,8,FStaplefield Drive in Brighton, has 38
OL,9,Fprevious convictions for 192 offences,
OL,10,Fmore than 150 of which are for similar
OL,11,Ffraud claims against businesses.
OL,13,FHe was sentenced to 26 weeks in
OL,14,Fprison, and the court also imposed a
OL,15,Fnew Criminal Behaviour Order (CBO) to
OL,16,Flast for five years.
OL,18,FThe CBO states that McEnroe must not
OL,19,Fmake a refund or compensation claim
OL,20,Ffrom any retail or food premises in
OL,21,FSussex.
